\section{\emph{alabaster}-based format, \code{AlabasterParam}}{


This stash format is the most complete and reliable way for long-term
(and portable) storage of an \code{MsExperiment}. Objects can be saved or read
from this stash format either using the \code{saveMsObject()} and \code{readMsObject()}
functions or also using the \code{\link[alabaster.base:saveObject]{alabaster.base::saveObject()}} and
\code{\link[alabaster.base:readObject]{alabaster.base::readObject()}} functions.
Data from the object's slots are stored to their respective folders (using
alabaster functionality). These folders are:
\itemize{
\item \emph{experiment_files}: the content of the \verb{@experimentFiles} slot, stored
as a \link{MsExperimentFilesStash}.
\item \emph{metadata}: the content of the object's \verb{@metadata} slot.
\item \emph{other_data}: the content of the object's \verb{@otherData} slot. Note that
export fails if object types are stored in this slot without available
\emph{alabaster} export functionality.
\item \emph{qdata}: the content of the object's \verb{@qdata} slot (if present). Currently
only \link[SummarizedExperiment:SummarizedExperiment]{SummarizedExperiment} objects are supported.
\item \emph{sample_data}: the object's \code{sampleData} data frame.
\item \emph{sample_data_links}: the content of the object's \verb{@sampleDataLinks} slot
defining the mapping between rows in \code{sampleData} and other entities in
the object, such as e.g. spectra.
\item \emph{sample_data_links_mcols}: the metadata content of the \verb{@sampleDataLinks}.
\item \emph{spectra}: the \link[Spectra:Spectra]{Spectra::Spectra} object with the MS data (if present).
The respective \link[SpectraStash:SpectraStash]{SpectraStash::SpectraStash} functionality is used to
export this data.
Note that not all \code{MsBackend} types might be supported. In that case,
the backend should be switched to one of the \code{MsBackend}s from the
\emph{Spectra} package using the \code{\link[Spectra:setBackend]{Spectra::setBackend()}} function.
}
}

\section{Text-file format, \code{PlainTextParam}}{


\code{MsExperiment} objects can also be saved to plain text files as a
MsExperimentStash in text file format. Note however that currently only some
of the object's content can be saved in that format. Content of slots
\verb{@qdata}, \verb{@metadata} and \verb{@otherData} (if present) are \strong{not} stored to the
stash. The text file-based stash directory contains the following files:
\itemize{
\item \emph{ms_experiment_sample_data.txt}: tabulator delimited text file with the
content of the \code{MsExperiment}'s \code{sampleData()}. This file is always saved.
\item \emph{ms_experiment_sample_data_links_\if{html}{\out{<linked slot>}}.txt}: a two column
tab-delimited text file with the mapping between rows in \code{sampleData()} and
elements in other slots of the \code{MsExperiment}. The name of the respective
slot is used as file name suffix. This file is only generated when \emph{sample
data links} are present.
\item \emph{ms_experiment_link_mcols.txt}: tab-delimited text file with the metadata
content of the \verb{@sampleDataLink} slot. This file is only generated when
\emph{sample data links} are present.
\item \emph{ms_experiment_files.txt}: the object's \link[MsExperiment:MsExperimentFiles]{MsExperiment::MsExperimentFiles}.
See \link{MsExperimentFilesStash} for information on the format. This file is
only generated if \code{experimentFiles()} are present in the object.
}

If the \code{MsExperiment} contained a \link[Spectra:Spectra]{Spectra::Spectra} object, it is saved
to the main \emph{MsExperimentStash} folder. A different set of files might be
stored, depending on the \code{MsBackend} used. This can also include raw MS data
files if parameter \code{consolidate = TRUE} is used in \code{saveMsObject()}.
See \link[SpectraStash:SpectraStash]{SpectraStash::SpectraStash} for more information.
}

\section{Retrieve MS data from \emph{MetaboLights}}{


In addition to the MsExperimentStash formats for storage of \code{MsExperiment}
objects, it is possible to load data from a metabolomics study directly
from the \href{https://www.ebi.ac.uk/metabolights/}{MetaboLights} repository.
See \link{MetaboLightsParam} for more information.
}

\examples{

## Example MS data files
library(Spectra)
library(MsExperiment)
library(MsDataHub)
fls <- c(X20171016_POOL_POS_1_105.134.mzML(),
    X20171016_POOL_POS_3_105.134.mzML())

## Create a MsExperiment for the two example files
mse <- readMsExperiment(fls, data.frame(name = c("A", "B"), index = 1:2))

## Define the path where to create the MsExperimentStash
d <- file.path(tempdir(), "ms_experiment_stash")

## Save the MsExperiment to a stash in alabaster format; Note: with
## `consolidate = TRUE` the MS data files are also copied into the
## stash
saveMsObject(mse, AlabasterParam(d), consolidate = TRUE)

## Show the content of the stash folder
library(fs)
dir_tree(d)

## Restore the object from the stash
res <- readMsObject(MsExperiment(), AlabasterParam(d))
res

sampleData(res)

spectra(res)
}
\seealso{
\link{MetaboLightsParam} for loading an \code{MsExperiment} from the
MetaboLights public repository.
}
